n* [http://www.library.hbs.edu/hc/ssb/index.html South Sea Bubble collection at Harvard University]\n* [https://sites.google.com/site/davesmant/monetary-economics/famous-first-bubbles/south-sea-bubble Famous First Bubbles \u2013 South Sea Bubble]\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106143016/http://www.thesouthseabubble.com/ |date=January 6, 2014 |title=Charles McKay's Account of The South Sea Bubble in Modern English}}\n* {{webarchive |date=2012-12-09 |url=https://archive.is/20121209151433/http://www.ehs.org.uk/ehs/conference2004/assets/paul.doc |title=Helen Paul's Account of The South Sea Company's slave trading activities}}\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01pcs5g The South Sea Bubble], audio programming with Melvyn Bragg and guests, BBC Radio 4.\n\n{{Corporate scandals}}\n{{Chartered companies}}\n{{Financial bubbles}}\n{{Financial crises}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1711 establishments in Great Britain]]\n[[Category:African slave trade]]\n[[Category:Age of Sail]]\n[[Category:Chartered companies]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1711]]\n[[Category:Corruption in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Defunct companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Economic bubbles]]\n[[Category:Economic history of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Financial crises]]\n[[Category:History of banking]]\n[[Category:Political scandals in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:South Sea Bubble]]\n", "name_user": "Blairall", "label": "safe", "comment": "link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sea_Company"}
{"title_page": "Honeymoon (2013 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Honeymoon\n| image          = Honeymoon (2013 film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jan H\u0159ebejk]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Petr Jarchovsk\u00fd]]\n| starring       = [[Anna Geislerov\u00e1]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Martin Strba\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|6|29|[[Karlovy Vary International Film Festival|Karlovy IFF]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 97 minutes\n| country        = Czech Republic\n| language       = Czech\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Honeymoon''''' ({{lang-cs|'''L\u00edb\u00e1nky'''}}) is a 2013 Czech [[drama film]] directed by [[Jan H\u0159ebejk]]. It was nominated for the [[Crystal Globe]] at the [[48th Karlovy Vary International Film Festival]], where H\u0159ebejk won the [[Best Director Award (Karlovy Vary IFF)|Best Director Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kviff.com/en/history/2013 |title=History 48th festival |work=kviff.com |accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref> The film was also screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section at the [[2013 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/honeymoon |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130816021345/http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/honeymoon |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 August 2013 |title=Honeymoon |accessdate=24 August 2013 |work=TIFF }}</ref><ref name=\"Indiewire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-adds-75-titles-to-2013-edition-james-franco-alex-gibney-hayao-miyazaki-sean-durkin-and-kevin-macdonald-among-them?page=2 |title=Toronto Adds 75+ Titles To 2013 Edition |accessdate=24 August 2013 |work=Indiewire}}</ref>\n\nAlong with ''[[Kawasaki's Rose]]'' and ''[[Innocence (2011 film)|Innocence]]'', with this film Hrebejk concludes his loose trilogy of films in which shadows from the past return to haunt the present of its characters.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Anna Geislerov\u00e1]] as Tereza\n* [[Stanislav Majer]] as Radim\n* [[Ji\u0159\u00ed \u010cern\u00fd (actor)|Ji\u0159\u00ed \u010cern\u00fd]] as Benda\n* [[Bo\u0159ivoj \u010cerm\u00e1k]] as Filip\n* [[Daniela Chod\u011brov\u00e1]] as Filip's mother\n* [[David M\u00e1j]] as Milan\n* [[Krist\u00fdna Nov\u00e1kov\u00e1]] as Renata\n* [[Juraj Nvota]] as Priest\n* [[Ji\u0159\u00ed \u0160est\u00e1k]] as Karel\n* [[Mat\u011bj Zik\u00e1n]] as Dominik\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.csfd.cz/film/325149-libanky/prehled/ ''L\u00edb\u00e1nky''] at csfd.cz\n* [https://www.kinobox.cz/film/315448-libanky ''L\u00edb\u00e1nky''] at kinobox.cz\n* {{IMDb title|2718538|Honeymoon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Honeymoon}}\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2013 drama films]]\n[[Category:Czech films]]\n[[Category:Czech-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Jan H\u0159ebejk]]\n[[Category:Czech drama films]]\n{{CzechRepublic-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Honeymoon\n| image          = Honeymoon (2013 film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Jan H\u0159ebejk]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Petr Jarchovsk\u00fd]]\n| starring       = [[Anna Geislerov\u00e1]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Martin Strba\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|6|29|[[Karlovy Vary International Film Festival|Karlovy IFF]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 97 minutes\n| country        = Czech Republic\n| language       = Czech\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Honeymoon''''' ({{lang-cs|'''L\u00edb\u00e1nky'''}}) is a 2013 Czech [[drama film]] directed by [[Jan H\u0159ebejk]]. It was nominated for the [[Crystal Globe]] at the [[48th Karlovy Vary International Film Festival]], where H\u0159ebejk won the [[Best Director Award (Karlovy Vary IFF)|Best Director Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kviff.com/en/history/2013 |title=History 48th festival |work=kviff.com |accessdate=22 March 2018}}</ref> The film was also screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section at the [[2013 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/honeymoon |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130816021345/http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/honeymoon |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 August 2013 |title=Honeymoon |accessdate=24 August 2013 |work=TIFF }}</ref><ref name=\"Indiewire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-adds-75-titles-to-2013-edition-james-franco-alex-gibney-hayao-miyazaki-sean-durkin-and-kevin-macdonald-among-them?page=2 |title=Toronto Adds 75+ Titles To 2013 Edition |accessdate=24 August 2013 |work=Indiewire}}</ref>\n\nAlong with ''[[Kawasaki's Rose]]'' and ''[[Innocence (2011 film)|Innocence]]'', with this film Hrebejk concludes his loose trilogy of films in which shadows from the past return to haunt the present of its characters.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Anna Geislerov\u00e1]] as Tereza\n* [[Stanislav Majer]] as Radim\n* [[Ji\u0159\u00ed \u010cern\u00fd (actor)|Ji\u0159\u00ed \u010cern\u00fd]] as Benda\n* [[Bo\u0159ivoj \u010cerm\u00e1k]] as Filip\n* [[Daniela Chod\u011brov\u00e1]] as Filip's mother\n* [[David M\u00e1j]] as Milan\n* [[Krist\u00fdna Nov\u00e1kov\u00e1]] as Renata\n* [[Juraj Nvota]] as Priest\n* [[Ji\u0159\u00ed \u0160est\u00e1k]] as Karel\n* [[Mat\u011bj Zik\u00e1n]] as Dominik\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.csfd.cz/film/325149-libanky/prehled/ ''L\u00edb\u00e1nky''] at csfd.cz\n* [https://www.kinobox.cz/film/315448-libanky ''L\u00edb\u00e1nky''] at kinobox.cz\n* {{IMDb title|2718538|Honeymoon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Honeymoon}}\n[[Category:2013 films]]